sorry for the poor picture quality, this was taken 6 years ago but I adore this picture and memory to go along with it. 
I don’t like to disclose my fears on social media but i have to let you know that I’m fucking terrified of bridges-not heights or the water below, just bridges. I don’t know why but I kind of attribute it back to with the 35W bridge collapsed years ago and that bridge is VERY familiar to me and drive across it often (while having minor panic attacks). Anyways, 6 years ago in New Zealand in the South Island I had to opportunity to bungee jump and decided I did NOT want to do it. After watching people I was traveling with sign up, I on a whim handed my credit card over and decided to bungee with @ajhackettbungynz 
I ended up diving off (I’ll post a video later) and it was such a liberating, freeing experience. And honestly, really helped with my fear of bridges haha! I’m sooooo happy I bought that ticket on a whim and desperately want to bungee again soon! 
Love you, New Zealand 😘
